  <h2>About Dār al-Ḥaqq</h2>

  <p>Dār al-Ḥaqq is a small, English-language reader of traditional Sunnī replies to common Salafī claims. Each topic is built around quoted excerpts from authoritative answers on SeekersGuidance, IslamQA.org, Ask Imam, and hadithanswers.com — the work belongs to those scholars and sites. Dār al-Ḥaqq simply gathers and frames it.</p>

  <p>The site is maintained by a student of traditional Sunnī ʿilm. It is not original fatwa, has no editorial board, and should not be taken as a replacement for asking a qualified scholar in your locality. Where the framing prose makes a claim that is not directly cited, treat it as the maintainer's reading of the broader Ashʿarī / Māturīdī tradition — verify with your shaykh.</p>

  <p>To suggest a topic, correct an error, or flag a misattributed quote, <a href="https://github.com/YusefB/darulhaqq/issues/new" rel="noopener external">open an issue on GitHub</a>. Corrections are taken seriously.</p>
</Base>
